description:
In order to facilitate the beta Apply for Healthy Start programme
  As a potential claimant
  I want to see the details of how my details are used and retained
name: Privacy notice page

elements.name: The back link on the Privacy notice page is not shown if we navigate to it directly

steps.name: I navigate to the privacy-notice page
the privacy-notice page is shown
no back link is shown

description:
In order to apply for the Apply for Healthy Start programme
  As a potential claimant
  I want to select whether or not I live in Scotland
name: Do you live in Scotland?

elements.name: Yes and No are displayed

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the do you live in Scotland page
Yes and No options are displayed on the do you live in Scotland page

elements.name: Do not select an option

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the do you live in Scotland page
I do not select an option
I click continue
I am informed that I need to select an option for do you live in Scotland

elements.name: Select the No option

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the do you live in Scotland page
I say No to the do you live in Scotland question
I click continue
I am shown the enter date of birth page
my session has not been destroyed

elements.name: Select the Yes option and claimant is told to use the Scottish scheme

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the do you live in Scotland page
I select the Yes option on the do you live in Scotland page
I click continue
I am shown the I live in Scotland page
I am informed that I cannot apply and should use the Scottish scheme
my session has been destroyed

elements.name: I can change my answer to yes for 'Do you live in Scotland?' from the check answers page

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the do you live in Scotland page
I am on the check answers page having entered valid details for a pregnant woman
I choose to change my answer to Do you live in Scotland
I select the Yes option on the do you live in Scotland page
I click continue
I am shown the I live in Scotland page
my session has been destroyed

description:
In order to apply for the Apply for Healthy Start programme
  As a potential claimant
  I want to select text or email to receive my code
name: We're going to send you a code

elements.name: Text and Email are displayed

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the send code page
Text and Email options are displayed on the send code page
The change text link points to the phone number page
The change email link points to the email address page

elements.name: Do not select an option

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the send code page
I do not select an option
I click continue
I am informed that I need to select an option for send code

elements.name: Select the Text option

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the send code page
I select Text as the method to receive the code
I click continue
I am shown the enter code page

elements.name: Select the Email option

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the send code page
I select Email as the method to receive the code
I click continue
I am shown the enter code page

description:
In order to apply for the Apply for Healthy Start programme

name: Terms and conditions

elements.name: I am prevented from submitting my application without accepting the terms and conditions

steps.name: I have entered my details up to the check answers page
I click continue without accepting the terms and conditions
I am told I must accept the terms and conditions

description:
In order to apply for the Apply for Healthy Start programme
  As a potential claimant
  If my claim is unsuccessful I want feedback about why my claim was unsuccessful
name: Unsuccessful application

elements.name: When a claimant applies for Apply for Healthy Start and is unsuccessful they are told why

I submit an application which returns a INELIGIBLE eligibility status

the page content displays that I am not eligible because my eligibility status is INELIGIBLE
